fragment

public final java.lang.String fragment()
Description copied from interface: JsonValue
Return the fragment identifier of this value. If this value has no parent container, returns "#". If this value has a parent, but that parent has no parent, returns "#key" where "key" is the value returned by key(), URL-encoded. If this value has a parent, and that parent has a parent, returns "#parent/key", where "#parent" is the fragment identifier of the parent of this value (which may itself be composed of several keys), and "key" is the value returned by key(), URL-encoded.

Specified by:
fragment in interface JsonValue
Returns:
The fragment identifier of this value.

put

public final JsonString put(java.lang.String key,
                            byte[] value)
Description copied from interface: JsonContainer
Put a binary value. The value will be base64-encoded and stored in a JsonString.

Note: The JsonString object will point to the underlying byte[] that was supplied; it will not copy it. The internal operations of the JsonSystem will not change it, but it will be made directly available through the JsonString object's JsonValue.binaryValue() method. So, if you need to make sure that the original is not changed, you must copy it before supplying it to this method.

Specified by:
put in interface JsonContainer
Parameters:
key - The key to put the value under.
value - The binary value to store.
